<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The controlling expression of the if statement is invariant: err is initialized from LFS_LOCK(lfs->cfg), and LFS_LOCK is defined as ((void)cfg,0) so err is always 0. Therefore the condition if (err) is always false (an invariant) and violates Rule 14.3. This is not covered by the allowed exceptions (not an infinite loop and not the permitted do-while case).
</scenario>
